14	Colorado Coalition for the Homeless	Colorado Coalition for the Homeless has worked to end homelessness in Colorado since 1985. One of the largest comprehensive homeless services organizations in the state, CCH serves through an integrated model of housing, healthcare, and supportive services.\n\nCCH operates federally qualified health centers, permanent supportive housing, and programs spanning street outreach, substance use recovery, employment services, and early childhood education.	https://www.coloradocoalition.org	https://res.cloudinary.com/dr3gnrygp/image/upload/v1772828923/qsk6aoptay88kwzv7jmc.png	{housing,health}	coloradocoalition	84-0951575	2026-02-28 21:34:25.259984	2026-03-18 20:44:05.17865	colorado-coalition-for-the-homeless	1984	https://www.coloradocoalition.org/volunteer	f	t	2111 Champa Street, Denver, CO 80205	https://www.coloradocoalition.org/donate	f	19,021 people received services\n14,721 patients received health care\n512 families served\n93% remained stably housed after one year\n73% reduction in emergency service costs for Housing First participants	CCH operates from a cluster of facilities in downtown Denver, with additional health centers across the metro area and a recovery campus in rural Las Animas County.	\N	\N	\N	(home)**Permanent Supportive Housing**CCH owns and operates 20+ residential properties across the Denver metro area, providing permanent supportive housing to thousands of households.\n(heart)**Federally Qualified Health Centers**A network of health centers providing primary care, dental, pharmacy, behavioral health, substance use treatment, and prenatal care to patients regardless of ability to pay.\n(sun)**Recovery Communities**Fort Lyon and Sage Ridge are large residential campuses offering up to two years of recovery-oriented transitional housing with integrated healthcare, vocational training, and peer support.\n(people)**Street Outreach and Support Services**The Denver Street Outreach Collaborative connects chronically homeless individuals to services through street medicine, case management, veterans programs, and employment assistance.	\N	\N	\N	f	\N
